This paper discusses a relational model for collaborative filtering and prediction of attributes in complex relational models. The paper focuses on the use of an infinite-dimensional latent variable as part of a Dirichlet process model, which is a common approach in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of the model in recommendation systems, which is a common application in database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the use of the model in a medical domain, which is a common application in social informatics (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the Chinese restaurant process for inference, which is a common approach in natural language processing (cs.CL).
